#PatriotDay #NeverForget #WeRemember911

node.text:
Today is the 20th anniversary of #Sept11. 

#OnthisDay in 2001, as millions watched the events unfolding in New York, American Airlines Flight 77 crashed into the Pentagon at 9:37 a.m.

Let us reflect on and pay tribute to the victims of 9/11 and all who sacrificed their lives in defense of America and freedom.

#NeverForget #WeRemember911 #PatriotDay

The Spartan Brigade is the only #airborne infantry brigade combat team in the #Arctic and #Pacific theaters, providing the unique capability to project an expeditionary force by #air. 

(Video by Maj. Jason Welch, 4th BCT, 25th Inf. Div.; Photos courtesy of Sheila de Vara, 673rd Public Affairs)

node.text:
Tomorrow is Flag Day!

The first celebration of the U.S. Flag's birthday was held in 1877 on the 100th anniversary of the Flag Resolution of 1777. However, it is believed that the first annual recognition of the flag's birthday dates back to 1885 when school teacher, BJ Cigrand, first organized a group of Wisconsin school children to observe June 14 - the 108th anniversary of the official adoption of The Stars and Stripes as the Flag's Birthday. Cigrand, now known as the 'Father of Flag Day,' continued to publically advocate the observance of June 14 as the flag's 'birthday', or 'Flag Day' for years.

Army outlined its plan today to fully comply with @deptofdefense order requiring all Service members to be fully vaccinated against #COVID19.

Active duty units are expected to be fully vaccinated by Dec. 15, 2021. Reserve and National Guard units are expected to be fully vaccinated by June 30, 2022.

#Soldiers may request administrative or medical exemptions as outlined in Army Regulations 600-20 and 40-562.

A @usarmyoldguard #Soldier takes part in military funeral honors for Army Cpl. Lloyd Odom at Arlington National Cemetery, Arlington, Va. 

Odom was reported missing in action on Dec. 2, 1950, when his unit was attacked by Chinese forces. He was taken prisoner and died of his wounds on Jan. 31, 1951.

📸 by Sgt. Nicholas T. Holmes
